   <mods:abstract>Drayton has been called a Jacobin in Porcupine's gazette; this is a result
            of his election to the state legislature at which time several Federalists lost their
            seats. Since he has been elected Lieutenant Governor he thought John Jay should be
            informed of the subject. As further proof, the only time he has been sued is by his
            cousin, Stephen Drayton, when the latter was arrested by a committee of the legislature
            for Jacobinical pursuits.</mods:abstract>
